2008-09-04 Thursday 23:54  mkgnu

	* src/lib/product/Glue/Subversion.pm.in (1.38,
	  SCMBUG_RELEASE_0-26-10), src/lib/product/Glue/Git.pm.in (1.4),
	  src/lib/product/Error.pm.in (1.45), configure.in (1.315): bug
	  992: Added functionality for capturing most of the commit
	  information on a post-commit Git hook. The hook does not supply
	  any arguments, but those can be extracted. e.g.

	  git-rev-parse HEAD

	    will give the commit hash of the last commit (the one that
	  triggered the hook)

	  git-log --no-walk

	    will give the log message and username

	  git-diff --name-status hash^ hash

	    will give the list of affected files.

	  The list of affected files is not being extracted yet.

