2007-12-28 Friday 21:59  mkgnu

	* configure.in (1.269): bug 1084: When using the 'wc' command, pipe
	  the output through awk to ensure no whitespace is prefixed before
	  the line count output. This requires autogenerating all scripts
	  that pipe output through the 'wc' command.

	  An alternative option would have been to simply remove the double
	  quotes around the output variable check of the 'wc' command, but
	  that could break the test scripts in ways that seemed unexpected
	  to a tester not familiar with this idiosynchracy of the shell.

